---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Framing - Design for the Continuum" activePage="framing">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="px-6 lg:px-24 py-12 lg:py-20">
    <h1 class="font-black text-3xl lg:text-[50px] leading-[1.1] max-w-[1400px]">
      Recent eco-juridical moves (e.g., rights of nature, more-than-human
      councils) extend standing to non-human beings yet leave largely unexamined
      the formation of the representer.
    </h1>
  </section>

  <!-- Posit Statement -->
  <section class="px-6 lg:px-24 py-12 lg:py-16">
    <h2 class="font-black text-3xl lg:text-[50px] leading-[1.2] max-w-[1400px]">
      I posit that before representation comes understanding and training
      representational subjectivity (even in a collective perspective).
    </h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Mobile Fixed Navigation for Research -->
  <div
    id="research-mobile-nav"
    class="fixed top-14 left-0 right-0 z-40 bg-(--bg-color) py-3 px-6 shadow-sm lg:hidden opacity-0 pointer-events-none transition-opacity duration-300"
  >
    <h3
      class="research-mobile-nav-item font-black text-xl leading-[1.1] mb-0.5 transition-opacity duration-300"
      data-target="section-problem"
    >
      Research Problem
    </h3>
    <h3
      class="research-mobile-nav-item font-black text-xl leading-[1.1] mb-0.5 opacity-20 transition-opacity duration-300"
      data-target="section-question"
    >
      Research Question
    </h3>
    <h3
      class="research-mobile-nav-item font-black text-xl leading-[1.1] opacity-20 transition-opacity duration-300"
      data-target="section-objectives"
    >
      Research Objectives
    </h3>
  </div>

  <!-- Research Sections Container -->
  <section class="research-container px-6 lg:px-24 py-12 lg:py-16 relative">
    <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 lg:gap-24">
      <!-- Desktop Sticky Sidebar -->
      <div class="lg:w-1/3 research-sidebar">
        <div class="hidden lg:block lg:sticky lg:top-24">
          <h3
            id="nav-problem"
            class="research-nav-item font-black text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2 transition-opacity duration-300"
            data-target="section-problem"
          >
            Research Problem
          </h3>
          <h3
            id="nav-question"
            class="research-nav-item font-black text-[60px] leading-[1.1] mb-2 opacity-20 transition-opacity duration-300"
            data-target="section-question"
          >
            Research Question
          </h3>
          <h3
            id="nav-objectives"
            class="research-nav-item font-black text-[60px] leading-[1.1] opacity-20 transition-opacity duration-300"
            data-target="section-objectives"
          >
            Research Objectives
          </h3>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Scrolling Content -->
      <div class="lg:w-2/3">
        <!-- Research Problem Content -->
        <div id="section-problem" class="research-section mb-24 lg:mb-40">
          <div
            class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] lg:leading-[30px] font-semibold max-w-[800px]"
          >
            <p class="mb-6">
              All living can be thought of as meeting (Buber) and when we are
              dealing with representation of MOTH subjectivity, an attitude of
              meeting the living as an intersubjective experience need
              necessarily be adopted.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-6">
              This is obviously a poetic as well as a political, or poethical
              approach. In Native Hawaiian world-making, an element of the
              world—wind, rock, ancestor, or place—is experienced as alive
              insofar as it participates in, and is carried by, the ongoing
              creation of stories.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-6">
              From this epistemological perspective, moʻolelo (story) is not
              just narrative but a living weave of relations.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-6">
              Reductionist mechanistic views are obsolete, we require ways of
              engaging with the world that present possibilities for co
              existance. For this, it is important to explore the whole range of
              intersubjective experiences, starting from the Ethics of care,
              which is about the relationship of respect and commitment for what
              is radically foreign to us. A relationship experienced firsthand,
              in the cognitive encounter "open and receptive" (p. 63) that makes
              experience the starting point for the development of new
              vocabularies. Nature, in fact, is not a given, but in the
              encounter, the subject experiences "a generative thinking that
              invents new paths for interpreting experience"
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Research Question Content -->
        <div id="section-question" class="research-section mb-24 lg:mb-40">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
            <!-- RQ1 -->
            <div class="relative">
              <div
                class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-pink to-transparent"
              >
              </div>
              <div class="pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓆ➀</h4>
                <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                  In what ways can we re-enchant human rationality and
                  relationality so that the threshold between the human and
                  (super)natural forces is unlearned?
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- RQ2 -->
            <div class="relative">
              <div
                class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-cyan-400 to-transparent"
              >
              </div>
              <div class="pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓆ➁</h4>
                <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                  What are the ways in which experiences can be designed,
                  curated (and measured) to act as a catalyst for the unlearning
                  of threshold and re-enchantment of human rationality and
                  relationality?
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- RQ3 -->
            <div class="relative">
              <div
                class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-green-400 to-transparent"
              >
              </div>
              <div class="pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓆ➂</h4>
                <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                  What kind of potentialities of engagement arise, after human
                  re-enchantment, from queering the relationship with MOTH?
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Research Objectives Content -->
        <div id="section-objectives" class="research-section">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
            <!-- RO1 -->
            <div class="relative">
              <div
                class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-pink to-transparent"
              >
              </div>
              <div class="pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓄ➀</h4>
                <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                  To select and analyze practices coming from Mediterranean
                  ancestral "continuum" communities, figuring out ways to learn
                  how their effects and affects can be measured
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- RO2 -->
            <div class="relative">
              <div
                class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-cyan-400 to-transparent"
              >
              </div>
              <div class="pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓄ➁</h4>
                <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                  To redesign and formulate approaches (ecopedagogy) training
                  the perspectives of a designer.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- RO3 -->
            <div class="relative">
              <div
                class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1 bg-gradient-to-b from-green-400 to-transparent"
              >
              </div>
              <div class="pl-6">
                <h4 class="font-black text-4xl lg:text-[60px] mb-4">ⓇⓄ➂</h4>
                <p class="text-lg lg:text-[25px] leading-[1.2] font-semibold">
                  To generate functional outcomes (like new ideas for
                  conservation, shifts in attitude or motives for stewardship)
                  at the personal and collective level of engagement with MOTH.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mobile Fixed Navigation for Methodology -->
  <div
    id="methodology-mobile-nav"
    class="fixed top-14 left-0 right-0 z-40 bg-charcoal text-cream py-3 px-6 shadow-sm lg:hidden opacity-0 pointer-events-none transition-opacity duration-300"
  >
    <h3
      class="methodology-mobile-nav-item font-black text-xl leading-[1.1] mb-0.5 transition-opacity duration-300"
      data-target="section-methodology"
    >
      Methodology
    </h3>
    <h3
      class="methodology-mobile-nav-item font-black text-xl leading-[1.1] opacity-30 transition-opacity duration-300"
      data-target="section-output"
    >
      Output
    </h3>
  </div>

  <!-- Methodology/Output Container - Dark Background -->
  <section
    class="methodology-container bg-charcoal text-cream px-6 lg:px-24 pt-16 lg:pt-24 pb-32 lg:pb-36 relative -mb-24 lg:-mb-28"
